      "comment": "BAKERS BANDIT (7) was having his first outing for close to seven weeks when less than 6 metres from the winner in second at Geelong last time. May need a bit of luck negotiating a very wide starting position but should strip fitter so has winning claims. YANKEE MOJOH (8) worked to find the lead and kept kicking to make it two wins in succession last time at Mt Gambier. Should enjoy a nice smother from this draw and will be looking for a split at some stage. Could land the hat trick if things go her way. STARZINHEREYES (2) draws better than when he worked and faded last time and was racing well prior. AMERICAN VICTORY (6) returns after eight months but produced some good results at this circuit last time in, winning over this distance three back. Can open this campaign with a positive effort.",
